.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-CONVERT-EXPORT-LAYOUT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.12.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-convert\-export\-layout \- Repair older dashboard export trees whose raw/ or prompt/ files were written under the leaf Grafana folder title instead of the full nested folder path, and rebuild legacy all\-orgs root indexes when child org exports are present but the root aggregate only describes one org.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard convert export-layout [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Repair older dashboard export trees whose raw/ or prompt/ files were written under the leaf Grafana folder title instead of the full nested folder path, and rebuild legacy all\-orgs root indexes when child org exports are present but the root aggregate only describes one org.
.PP
Use this when an existing export already has correct raw/folders.json metadata, but files are laid out like raw/Infra/CPU__uid.json instead of raw/Platform/Team/Infra/CPU__uid.json. This is an offline artifact repair; it does not contact Grafana.
.SH BEFORE / AFTER
.IP \(bu 2
Before: old exports flatten nested Grafana folders that share the same leaf title.
.IP \(bu 2
After: repaired raw/ and prompt/ lanes mirror the Grafana folder path recorded in raw/folders.json.
.IP \(bu 2
Before: old all\-orgs roots can list only one org at the root while sibling org_* directories contain more dashboards.
.IP \(bu 2
After: the root aggregate is rebuilt from child org indexes with scopeKind=all\-orgs\-root, orgCount, and orgs[].
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-input\-dir
existing dashboard export root or variant directory.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-dir
write a repaired copy without touching the original export.
.TP
.B \-\-in\-place
repair the input tree directly.
.TP
.B \-\-backup\-dir
required with \-\-in\-place; stores changed files before moving them.
.TP
.B \-\-variant
repair only raw or prompt; repeat the flag to select both. Defaults to both.
.TP
.B \-\-raw\-dir
raw lane used as metadata source for prompt\-only repair.
.TP
.B \-\-folders\-file
explicit folder inventory file.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
render the move plan without writing files.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
allow existing output files to be replaced.
.TP
.B \-\-show\-operations
show each MOVE, SAME, BLOCKED, and EXTRA operation when using text output.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
render text, table, csv, json, or yaml.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Repair older dashboard export trees whose raw/ or prompt/ files were written under the leaf Grafana folder title instead of the full nested folder path, and rebuild legacy all\-orgs root indexes when child org exports are present but the root aggregate only describes one org.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard convert export-layout --input-dir ./dashboards --output-dir ./dashboards.fixed --dry-run --output-format table
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1)
